    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "35adce6e_6a11b670",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
        "patchSetId": 25
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 333
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T15:56:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No. RDMA_TXQ_INVALID_BUF (~0) is only ever written to extra WQEBBs of multi-WQEBB TSO WQEs — ring slots that do not own a buffer index. The non-TSO send_regular: path always stores a real bi[] value; vlib buffer indices are pool offsets that can never reach ~0. A clarifying comment has been added.",
      "parentUuid": "167702ec_a6f9b76f",
      "revId": "f2e8858fa2d5256d6cd3c47887b91ca53b70557c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aed596fa_0a7fa7a4",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
        "patchSetId": 25
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T10:20:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why this change? This should not happen? Do we leak buffer in the error case?",
      "revId": "f2e8858fa2d5256d6cd3c47887b91ca53b70557c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4cea2a86_2fb3fab1",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
        "patchSetId": 25
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 333
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T15:56:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No buffers are leaked. comp_tail is read from wqe-\u003ectrl.imm, which was written by the driver at WQE post time. If the bounds check fails, either the CQE wqe_counter or ctrl.imm is corrupted, so we cannot trust comp_tail to determine which range to free. Skipping the free and leaving txq-\u003ehead unchanged is intentional: those buffers will be reclaimed on the next valid completion that advances head past them. A comment now documents this reasoning.",
      "parentUuid": "aed596fa_0a7fa7a4",
      "revId": "f2e8858fa2d5256d6cd3c47887b91ca53b70557c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a097a9ae_36eb433f",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
        "patchSetId": 25
      },
      "lineNbr": 267,
      "author": {
        "id": 361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T10:20:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "isnt lkey already big-endian here?",
      "revId": "f2e8858fa2d5256d6cd3c47887b91ca53b70557c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "021f1e86_061a5606",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
        "patchSetId": 25
      },
      "lineNbr": 267,
      "author": {
        "id": 333
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T15:56:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No. rdma_mlx5_wqe_init_tso() receives rd-\u003elkey in host-endian (see call site: rdma_mlx5_wqe_init_tso(..., rd-\u003elkey)) and the clib_host_to_net_u32() at line 267 is correct.\n\nThe confusion comes from the local variable also named lkey rdma_device_output_tx_mlx5_chained (line 290: const u32 lkey \u003d clib_host_to_net_u32(rd-\u003elkey); ), which *is* already big-endian. That variable has been renamed to lkey_be in this patchset to make the distinction explicit.",
      "parentUuid": "a097a9ae_36eb433f",
      "revId": "f2e8858fa2d5256d6cd3c47887b91ca53b70557c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
